Tombini Says Brazil Aims to Meet Inflation Target by Dec. 2012

-- B y   A r n a l d o   G a l v a o
-- 
2011-09-27T15:22:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/tombini-says-brazil-aims-to-meet-inflation-target-by-dec-2012.html
Brazil ’s policy makers are seeking
to bring inflation back to the 4.5 percent target by December
2012, central bank President Alexandre Tombini said.  Tombini, speaking to senators in Brasilia, said there are
clear signs demand is slowing and that current inflation is in
line with the government’s target.  To contact the reporter on this story:
